OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772881499
OL,3,CIndonesia moves to ban social media
OL,4,Cfor under-16s
OL,6,FDenmark, France, Greece, Italy and
OL,7,FSpain are jointly testing age
OL,8,Fverification software in collaboration
OL,9,Fwith the European Commission, with a
OL,10,Fview to making an age verification app.
OL,12,FIn the UK, children under the age of
OL,13,F13 are currently restricted from
OL,14,Fhaving social media, but it's
OL,15,Festimated 2.5 million of them have
OL,16,Faccounts, according to Ofcom.
OL,18,FStatistics from Ofcom also showed that
OL,19,F37% of children aged three to five use
OL,20,Fsocial media, with 60% having their
OL,21,Fown social media profile.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
